### Authentication Examples
# This file demonstrates various authentication methods supported by nrest.nvim

### Example 1: Bearer Token Authentication
# Syntax: @auth bearer <token>
@auth bearer mytoken123

GET https://httpbin.org/bearer
Accept: application/json

### Example 2: Basic Authentication
# Syntax: @auth basic <username> <password>
@auth basic myuser mypassword

GET https://httpbin.org/basic-auth/myuser/mypassword
Accept: application/json

### Example 3: API Key Authentication
# Syntax: @auth apikey <header-name> <api-key>
@auth apikey X-API-Key secret123

GET https://httpbin.org/get
Accept: application/json

### Example 4: Digest Authentication
# Syntax: @auth digest <username> <password>
@auth digest testuser testpass

GET https://httpbin.org/digest-auth/auth/testuser/testpass
Accept: application/json

### Example 5: Bearer Token with Variables
@token = my-secret-token-123
@auth bearer {{token}}

GET https://httpbin.org/bearer
Accept: application/json

### Example 6: Basic Auth with System Environment Variables
# Set environment variables: export API_USER=myuser API_PASS=mypass
@auth basic $API_USER $API_PASS

GET https://httpbin.org/basic-auth/myuser/mypass
Accept: application/json

### Example 7: API Key from Environment Variable
@apiKey = $MY_API_KEY
@auth apikey X-API-Key {{apiKey}}

GET https://httpbin.org/get
Accept: application/json

### Example 8: POST Request with Bearer Authentication
@auth bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9

POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

### Example 9: Multiple Headers with API Key Auth
@auth apikey X-Custom-Auth-Token custom-secret-123

GET https://httpbin.org/get
Accept: application/json
User-Agent: nrest.nvim
X-Request-ID: 12345

### Example 10: Bearer Token from Environment File
# Create .env.http with: @AUTH_TOKEN = your-token-here
# Configure in setup: env_file = '.env.http'
@auth bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

GET https://api.github.com/user
Accept: application/json

